710458f-a.text:
Tenth Avenue, north from West 14th Street, showing the thoroughfare that is popularly known as "Hell-road or Death Avenue."  Train tracks in the foreground determined that appellation.  At the left, are the National Biscuit Co. Building and the Merchants Refrigerating Co. plant.  The former also occupy the structure on the right.  The one story garage between 14th and 15th Sts. has only recently been completed.

July 24, 1924

Standard Photographic Service
Gift of Borough President of Manhatten

711310f-a.text:
14th Street, at and adjoining SE corner of Tenth Avenue, showing a branch of Armour & Company, packers, in the old buildings on the corner, and the new building adjoining, constructed with a passage through it fro the New York Central Railroad's new elevated line which is about to be built down along the lower west side.
July 16, 1932
P.L. Sperr

710459f-a.text:
(1)
Tenth Ave., (right), north from and including West 14th Street, showing the National Biscuit Co. plant at West 15th extending to 16th Streets, and also facing on Eleventh Ave. (left). Two bridges connect the main plant, with a new annex; through which pass the elevated tracks of the N.Y. Central R.R. Also shown (left), is a portion of the elevated West Side Vehicular Highway, running north on Eleventh Ave.
March 31, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, showing a view slightly eastward.
March 31, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

710460f-b.text:
(1)
Tenth Avenue, east side, north from 14th Street. The front of the National Biscuit Company Building has been demolished for the construction of the elevated trestle of the New York
Central railroad.
March 16, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same.
September 6, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same. A filling station now occupies the N.E. corner of 14th Street, the New York Central elevated trestle has been erected, and the National Biscuit Company has extended the front of its building to Tenth Avenue, to replace that part of the old building which was demolished for the railroad
structure.
June 20, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
